# Verify Docker build after changes

The MIPS cross-compiler runs **inside Docker only**. Host `build/` artifacts are often invalid (e.g. empty `patch.elf` → objcopy "file format not recognized").

After editing firmware sources, linker scripts, `Makefile`, `pack.py`, or `pad.py`:

```bash
cd rtl8761bu-libre
docker build -t rtl8761bu-libre .
docker run --rm -v "$(pwd)":/work rtl8761bu-libre make docker
```

`make docker` runs `clean all verify` and must succeed before considering the change done.

Variants:

```bash
docker run --rm -v "$(pwd)":/work rtl8761bu-libre make minimal verify
```

Do not rely on bare `make all` on the host unless `mipsel-linux-gnu-gcc` is installed.
